  "texts": [
    "3 and 4 of the Copyright in the Digital Single Market Directive (CDSM).",
    "76 As more extensively discussed elsewhere, 77 the temporary copying exception of Art.",
    "5(1) has historically represented the balancing mechanism between the protection of rightholders' interest on the one hand and the right of users to technological development and innovation on the other hand.",
    "This is visible both in the legislative history of the provision 78 as well as in the more recent interpretation offered by the CJEU.",
    "79 Article 5(1) however is limited in various ways, chiefly in that it is an exception only to temporary acts of reproduction, thus permanent copies -which are fundamental for the replicability of machine learning results -are excluded from its scope."
  ],
